<p>100. With regard to the issue of compensation to the family of the victims, the Special 
Rapporteur takes note of the Government&#8223;s reply that the existing criminal procedure 
</p>
<p>legislation in Ukraine does not provide for granting material or any other assistance to the 
victim&#8223;s family. In this regard, he would like to reiterate that the families and dependents of 
victims of extra-legal, arbitrary or summary executions shall be entitled to fair and adequate </p>

<p><b>A/HRC/23/47/Add.5 
</b></p>
<p> <b>61 
</b></p>
<p>compensation within a reasonable period of time. He calls upon the Government of Ukraine 
